# audit-pii patterns — local-only template.
#
# Copy this file to .audit-pii-patterns (which is gitignored) and add the
# tokens you don't want leaking to a public repo. The script reads it before
# every git push and blocks if any match is found anywhere in the tree.
#
# Bootstrap:
#   cp .audit-pii-patterns.example .audit-pii-patterns
#   $EDITOR .audit-pii-patterns
#
# Format:
#   - One ERE regex per line (egrep / grep -E syntax)
#   - Blank lines and lines starting with # are ignored
#   - Pattern matching is case-insensitive
#   - Use \b for word boundaries to avoid sub-string false positives
#     (e.g. \bwife\b won't match "wifeless")
#
# Suggested categories:
#   - First names of household members / family / collaborators you want kept private
#   - Family-relationship words you treat as identifying (wife, spouse, kids, child)
#   - Specific locations (street addresses, neighborhoods narrower than city)
#   - Account handles you keep separate from this repo
#   - Old persona anchor slugs you've since renamed
#
# Examples (DELETE THESE — they're illustrative only):
# \bspouse_first_name\b
# \bchild_first_name\b
# \bwife\b
# \bkids?\b
# \bchild\b
# WAF
# \bhomeschool\b
# 123\s+main\s+st
# my-handle-on-other-platforms
